04949nam a22008535i 9783110989465DE-B159720230529101353.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230529t20222022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2022941403  a97831109894657 a10.1515/97831109894652doi  a(DE-B1597)634057  a(OCoLC)1344538967  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aB4378.C5bM55 202204a232.092223/eng/202211141 aMillay, Thomas J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Abased Christ :bA New Reading of Kierkegaard’s 'Practice in Christianity' /cThomas J. Millay. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (XIV, 149 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aKierkegaard Studies. Monograph Series ,x1434-2952 ;v4600tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgements -- tAbbreviations -- tPreface -- tChapter One: Preliminary Matters: Context, Title, Structure, Author -- tChapter Two: Abasement -- tChapter Three: Contemporaneity -- tChapter Four: Imitation -- tChapter Five: Kierkegaard and Womanist Theology -- tConclusion -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Abased Christ is the first monograph to be devoted exclusively to Søren Kierkegaard’s Christological masterpiece, Practice in Christianity. Alongside an argument for a new translation of the work’s title, it offers detailed textual commentary on a series of themes in Practice in Christianity, such as the person of Christ, contemporaneity, imitation, and Kierkegaard’s philosophy of history. Anti-Climacus, the pseudonymous author of Practice in Christianity, presents to his readers a uniquely challenging understanding of who Christ is and what it means to follow him. The Christ of Anti-Climacus is not the glorious Christ who abides with the Father in heaven, but the abased Christ who is poor, marginal, offensive, and persecuted. Throughout Practice in Christianity, we are called not only to perceive the abased Christ, but to follow after him. The Abased Christ aims to enrich historical theologians’ appreciation of Kierkegaard’s Christology. However, it concludes by grappling with questions of power, agency, and sacrifice which have been at the forefront of contemporary theology in the 20th and 21st centuries, thereby suggesting how we might make sense of Kierkegaard’s Christology today.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSufferingxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 4aChristologie. 4aGeschichtsphilosophie. 4aKierkegaard, Søren. 4aTheologie.  aChristology.  aKierkegaard.  aphilosophy of history.  atheology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z978311076682008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishz978311099454408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831109895190 cprintz978311099971640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311098946540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110989465423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110989465/original  a978-3-11-076682-0  DG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099454-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alle